I've always been impressed with the quality of food at Verandah.
We started off with the Capasanta (Diver Scallops, Cauliflower Puree, Almond, Saba ).
These scallops are to die for!
They are cooked to perfection and it leaves you wanting more.
We also ordered the Insalata Aragosta (Lobster, Frisee, Summer Vegetables, Truffle Vinaigrette).
I loved the presentation of this dish with whole pieces of lobster that you could see.
However, I don't think I'm a fan of the summer veggies only because it left a lil zing in my mouth.
I'm sure other people enjoy that zing, but I don't care for it.
For the main course I decided to go with the Halibut Putanesca (Tuscan Vegetables and Tomato Olive Sauce) and the boyfriend ordered the Brasato Di Barolo (Braised Short-Ribs, White Polenta, Gouda Fondue).
My halibut had a slightly crispy outer shell and a flaky core.
It was absolutely divine.
The short ribs were melt in your mouth tender.
To top it all off, we decided to go with the Cannoli flight.
By then I was so full that I'm not sure I enjoyed it as much as I should have, but it was  très délicieux.
I will be back for more!

