We never had to leave the hotel for meals, a reflection of quality in this competitive restaurant town, rather than convenience or laziness.
The kids that I've witnessed have always been well-behaved, probably experienced and comfortable in the atmosphere of Four Seasons.
It is not a family restaurant for unbehaved, noisy children.

